The Warden got out of the ship as fast as he could.  He and Celeron met in mid-air about half way between the two places and they were both almost hit by the firepower of the angry prisoner.

&quot;Why would you imprison somebody with their weapons still weapons?&quot; Celeron angrily asked Tigon (the warden).

Tigon hadn&#39;t waited to listen to Celeron, he was already locked in a battle with the prisoner.

The prisoner fired a volley of three shots which hit Tigon in the chest.  Tigon blasted the prisoner with his main gun, and then kicked the prisoner out of the air.

Celeron decided to sneak over to the pod and see what he could learn.

The prisoner got back up and got up real close to Tigon.

&quot;You won&#39;t take me back!  NEVER!&quot; at that, he started firing violently.

Tigon tried to shield his face with his arm; he tripped and fell over backwards down a hill.  The prisoner saw his chance and jumped on Tigon.

Celeron decided to intervene (there would always be time to pick through the pod later) he charged up his arm cannons and sneaked up behind the raging prisoner.  Tigon was not moving and the prisoner was trying to break open the armor on his back.  Celeron fired both of his cannons pointblank into the prisoner.  He was blown back a few yards and fell into the sand.

Celeron decided that if he didn&#39;t act now, he&#39;d lose too and could possibly die.  He grabbed a pair of handcuffs from Tigon&#39;s tools, and he shot at the prisoner to make sure he was down.  When cuffed the prisoner, the prisoner tried to break free.  Tigon reactivated just in time to see Celeron attempting to disarm the prisoner.

&quot;This prisoner has a protective field that keeps him from being disarmed.  The only way I could detain him, was to render him unconscious.&quot;

The prisoner was still struggling, Tigon took a device from his kit and strapped it to the prisoner&#39;s neck.

&quot;Now we can momentarily control him.&quot; Tigon explained.

Celeron kicked the prisoner who was now powerless to resist him.  Tigon glared at Celeron and Celeron immediately stopped.

When they got back into the ship The Warden chained the prisoner to the wall and had Celeron guard him.  Tigon then prepared a chamber to keep the prisoner in.

&quot;Hey...isn&#39;t there some way to disarm him?&quot; Celeron asked.

&quot;I haven&#39;t found a way to.  I&#39;ve been trying for several years.  He has an energon field that is generated when someone tries to tamper with his weapons.  I&#39;ve given up trying&quot;

Celeron thought that this was a challenge worth trying.  He rubbed his hands together and schemed.


